      "6df75662-428a-4ed0-872d-6215e3c3809a/structure-tensor/local-window-sigma" : {
        "name" : "Local window σ",
        "description" : "The structure tensor computes the orientation and isotropy properties in a local window. Here, the local window is characterized by a 2D Gaussian function of standard deviation σ. The parameter σ (expressed in pixel unit) is a critical parameter that determines the scale of the analysis. It should have a value roughly close to the structure of interest (e.g. thickness of the filament)"
      },
